<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nurse Accused of Taking Beanie Baby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HERSHEY, Pa. (AP) -- Authorities have accused a former nurse of  
stealing a Beanie Baby toyrom a 12-year-old girl's hospital bed 
while the girl was recovering from open-heart surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	``I just was very floored that it would happen,'' said Michele  
Kiser, the mother of patient Nicole Kiser. ``I just could not 
believe that someone would steal from a sick child.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Police said former Hershey Medical Center nurse Suzanne E.  
Pinkney, 50, stole the ``Halo the angel bear'' Beanie Baby from the 
child Dec. 8, then later struggled with officers who confronted 
her. 
</P>
<P>
	She was charged last week with theft by unlawful taking,  
resisting arrest and disorderly conduct. 
</P>
<P>
	Nicole, who nearly died from a closed heart valve and  
complications, was given the $70 toy as a gift. Police have since 
returned it to her. 
</P>
<P>
	Hershey Medical Center officials would say only that Ms. Pinkney  
no longer works there. Ms. Pinkney, who faces a July court hearing, 
could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
