<HEADLINE> May Department Stores To Expand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- May Department Stores Co. will open 18 new  
stores as part of its $500 million expansion plan. 
</P>
<P>
	Two of the stores already have opened. The St. Louis-based  
company also will remodel 29 stores, which includes expansions in 
23 locations. 
</P>
<P>
	The plan was unveiled at the annual shareholders meeting, where  
May announced record sales and earnings per share for the 24th 
consecutive year. Sales were $13.1 billion for a 6.4 percent 
increase and earnings per share increased 11.1 percent to $2.30. 
</P>
<P>
	The company opened 29 new stores last year.  
</P>
<P>
	May operates 394 department stores in 32 states and the District  
of Columbia. 

