<DOCNO> APW19990521.0025 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-21 06:31:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Greenberg Named McDonald's Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- McDonald's Corp. has named Jack Greenberg, who  
has been credited with helping the fast-food chain make a sharp 
turnaround in recent months, as its chairman. 
</P>
<P>
	Greenberg, who had been the company's president and chief  
executive, becomes only the fourth chairman since McDonald's was 
founded in 1955. His promotion was announced at McDonald's annual 
shareholders meeting Thursday and is effective immediately. 
</P>
<P>
	Greenberg, 56, replaces Michael R. Quinlan, 54, who will remain  
a member of McDonald's board and chairman of its executive 
committee. 
</P>
<P>
	Greenberg will relinquish the title of president but said the  
company won't actively seek another executive to fill the position. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want you to know that I have total passion for this  
business,'' Greenberg told shareholders. ``We clearly see the 
growth opportunities that are ahead of us, and we will pursue them 
relentlessly.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts have praised Greenberg for steering the chain in the  
right direction over the past year. 
</P>
<P>
	After months of struggling sales and declining domestic market  
share, the chain last year gained market share and boosted sales at 
stores open at least a year, in part because of such successful 
promotions as Beanie Babies and Monopoly. The company's stock has 
soared more than 30 percent under his tenure. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts say McDonald's has experienced a remarkable turnaround  
as it decentralized its domestic operations to give grumbling 
franchisees more say in developing their menus and planning 
promotions. 
</P>
<P>
	Greenberg also has given the green light for McDonald's to  
explore other restaurant concepts. The company early last year 
purchased a stake in fast-growing Mexican food chain Chipotle 
Mexican Grill and last month purchased Aroma Ltd., a British chain 
of 23 shops that sell coffee and sandwiches in a lively atmosphere 
of recorded Caribbean music and bright yellow and orange decor. 
This month, it purchased the privately owned Donatos Pizza chain of 
143 restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
	The company also has benefited from increased expansion  
overseas, particularly in Europe, where revenues have exceeded 
domestic sales in recent years and where expansion still is 
occurring rapidly. 
</P>
<P>
	Greenberg has served as McDonald's president and chief executive  
officer since April 1998. He joined the company in 1982 as 
executive vice president and chief financial officer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
