<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bonds Rise Sharply After Worry / Bonds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Bonds rose sharply Friday after a week of worry  
about rising inflation and interest rates. 
</P>
<P>
	The price of the benchmark 30-year Treasury bond rose 1 1/32  
point, or $10.31 1/4 per $1,000 in face value. Its yield, which moves 
in the opposite direction, dropped to 5.75 percent, down from late 
Thursday's 5.83 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds have struggled over the past week after a report on May 14  
showed a surprisingly big jump in consumer prices during April. 
Then, on Tuesday, the Federal Reserve revealed a shift in stance 
toward boosting interest rates to slow the economy and protect 
against inflation. 
</P>
<P>
	The news has weighed heavily on fixed-income investments, which  
are less appealing in times of inflation or when rising interest 
rates make the payoff on existing bonds less attractive. 
</P>
<P>
	In other trading Friday, prices of short-term Treasuries ranged  
from 1/8 to 1/4 point higher, and intermediate maturities ranged from 
7/16 to 23/32 point higher, reported Bridge Telerate. 
</P>
<P>
	Yields on three-month Treasury bills fell to 4.59 percent from  
late Thursday's 4.60 percent, while its discount fell 0.01 
percentage point to 4.47 percent. Six-month yields were unchanged 
at 4.75 percent as the discount held steady at 4.57 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	One-year yields dropped to 4.81 percent from late Thursday's  
4.85 percent, while the discount fell 0.03 percentage point to 4.59 
percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Yields are the interest bonds pay by maturity, while the  
discount is the interest at which they are sold. 
</P>
<P>
	The federal funds rate, the interest on overnight loans between  
banks, fell to 4.69 percent from 4.75 percent late Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	In the tax-exempt market, the Bond Buyer index of 40 actively  
traded municipal bonds rose 3/16 point 122 7/32. The average yield 
to maturity edged lower to 5.35 percent from late Thursday's 5.36 
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
