<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Location of Kosovo Refugees in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	With the arrival of 483 more Kosovo refugees at Fort Dix, N.J.,  
the number now in the United States has reached 4,198, of whom 693 
have been placed in homes in 16 states, the State Department said. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. government has offered to take in up to 20,000 refugees  
from camps in Macedonia, where they fled from their homes in the 
Yugoslav province of Kosovo. Officials say 450 more are to arrive 
in the next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Here is where the current Kosovo refugees are living:  
</P>
<P>
	At Fort Dix, awaiting processing, 3,505.  
</P>
<P>
	Arizona, 11.  
</P>
<P>
	California, 65.  
</P>
<P>
	Connecticut, 11.  
</P>
<P>
	Florida, 50.  
</P>
<P>
	Idaho, 6.  
</P>
<P>
	Illinois, 20.  
</P>
<P>
	Kentucky, 14.  
</P>
<P>
	Michigan, 26  
</P>
<P>
	New Jersey, 81.  
</P>
