<HEADLINE> 5 Boys Charged For Raping Twin Girls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Kan. (AP) -- Five boys were charged today in the  
alleged rape and sodomy of 6-year-old twin girls at a day-care 
center. 
</P>
<P>
	The suspects, four 13-year-old boys and one 11-year-old boy,  
sexually assaulted the girls on May 15 in the basement of a day 
care center and in a shed next door, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
	The girls were apparently alone in the center and unattended by  
any adult, police said. The next day, the girls told their mother 
about the alleged assault and they were taken to the hospital for 
tests. 
</P>
<P>
	``They saw the girls were available and took advantage of  
them,'' Lt. Doug Hansen said. 
</P>
<P>
	Two of the suspects are the sons of the owner of a woman who  
runs the day care center and lives next door to the center, police 
said. The other three are friends of her sons. 
</P>
<P>
	Each of the boys was charged in juvenile court with six counts  
of aggravated criminal sodomy. Two of them were also charged with 
two counts of rape. 
</P>
<P>
	Arrest warrants were issued Friday but the boys were not yet in  
custody. 
</P>
<P>
	The day-care center was closed by order of the state on  
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
