<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Takes Two-Week Vacation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- After winning another major political victory over  
his hard-line foes, Boris Yeltsin left today for two weeks of 
vacation in southern Russia, his spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
	Yeltsin will vacation in the Black Sea resort town of Sochi,  
presidential spokesman Dmitry Yakushkin said. 
</P>
<P>
	The vacation comes after Yeltsin ousted the Cabinet last week,  
faced down an impeachment vote on Saturday and saw his loyalist 
premier-designate, Sergei Stepashin, easily approved by the lower 
house of parliament Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Yeltsin has rested several times in Sochi. He was there in  
November to recover from what aides described as fatigue and high 
blood pressure. 
</P>
<P>
	The president was reportedly sick with bronchitis earlier this  
week, but he denies he has any serious health problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
