<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> New Web Site Offered to Realtors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	REDMOND, Wash. (AP) -- Microsoft Corp.'s HomeAdvisor and  
Homeseekers.com are offering free Web pages to real estate agents 
nationwide in an effort to catch up to industry leader Realtor.com, 
the Web site of the National Association of Realtors. 
</P>
<P>
	The alliance allows agents to create their own Web page hosted  
by Homeseekers.com with personalized links to HomeAdvisor services, 
the companies in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Each page will include the agent's picture, contact information  
and a personalized Web address. Users will be able to view home 
listings and check on neighborhood and financing information. 
</P>
<P>
	Homeseekers.com, based in Minden, Nev., says it has about  
680,000 listings on its Web site. HomeAdvisor, part of 
Redmond-based Microsoft's MSN Network, has more than 500,000, 
according to The Washington Post. 
</P>
<P>
	``This announcement significantly changes the online real estate  
landscape,'' said John Tuccillo, former chief economist for the 
National Association of Realtors. 
</P>
<P>
	HomeAdvisor.com had 493,000 visitors in March and  
Homeseekers.com had 123,000, compared to Realtor.com's 1.7 million, 
according to a Media Metrix survey in today's Washington Post. 
</P>
</TEXT>
