<HEADLINE> Horse Trainer Gene Jacobs Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Retired thoroughbred trainer Gene Jacobs has  
died at age 86. 
</P>
<P>
	He died at his home in New York on Thursday after a long battle  
with Parkinson's disease. He was a brother of Hall of Fame trainer 
Hirsch Jacobs, 
</P>
<P>
	Gene retired in 1989 after 45 years as a trainer.  
</P>
<P>
	He trained Sheila's Reward to the sprint championship in 1951  
and 1952. 
</P>
<P>
	Jacobs' wife, Mildred, died several years ago. His survivors  
include a son, Steven, and a daughter, Elisabeth. 
</P>
<P>
	A graveside ceremony will be held Sunday in Brooklyn.  
</P>
</TEXT>
