<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Houston's Caminiti Injured in Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Houston third baseman Ken Caminiti strained  
his right calf while stealing a base and was forced to leave Friday 
night's game against San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
	Caminiti, who began the night batting .287 with two homers and  
16 RBIs, was listed as day-to-day. 
</P>
<P>
	Caminiti hit an RBI single in the third inning and tried to  
steal second. As he neared the base, he appeared to cramp up and 
grabbed his right leg, but still managed to slide around shortstop 
Rich Aurilia's tag. 
</P>
<P>
	Team trainers went on to the field to assist Caminiti, and he  
limped off the field and into the clubhouse. He was replaced in the 
lineup by Jack Howell. 
</P>
</TEXT>
