<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-21 16:41:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Link To IOC Scholarships on Tax Form </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- The Salt Lake Organizing Committee finally  
filed its 1997-98 tax return, the first to acknowledge that the 
committee provided scholarships, most of which can be traced to the 
relatives of International Olympic Committee members. 
</P>
<P>
	However, tax attorneys issued a disclaimer that the payments of  
tuition, room and board do not meet the Internal Revenue Service 
definition of a ``scholarship program,'' and still are not reported 
that way, The Salt Lake Tribune said in a copyright story on 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Revelations of a scholarship last winter triggered multiple  
investigations into how Salt Lake won the bid for the 2002 Winter 
Games and its continued pampering of IOC members and their 
relatives. 
</P>
<P>
	Past tax returns have put the so-called scholarships in ``other  
costs,'' and that's the proper category, said Albert Rodriguez, 
whose Los Angeles law firm Rodriguez, Horii and Choi was hired by 
the SLOC late last year. The SLOC referred all questions to 
Rodriguez on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The latest tax return gives much more detail on revenue and  
spending than past returns. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez declined to characterize past tax returns as sloppy or  
inadequate, but characterized the latest return ``an extra effort 
in the interest of complete and full disclosure.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He declined to say whether he has advised the committee to amend  
its previous tax returns. 
</P>
<P>
	The carefully crafted response -- and the length of time it took  
accountants to file it -- reflects the delicate situation in which 
SLOC finds itself. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. Justice Department is investigating whether lavish  
spending on IOC members and their relatives constitutes a crime. 
Also at issue is whether SLOC and the bid committee falsified tax 
returns or abused their tax-exempt status. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990521.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-21 17:21:24 </DATE_TIME>
