<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Red Sox Pitcher Throws Fake Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Red Sox pitcher Ramon Martinez threw 84 pitches in  
a simulated game today for the first time since he underwent 
shoulder surgery last June. 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez said he felt no pain after throwing and gained  
confidence about returning to the rotation. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm very happy,'' Martinez said. ``I don't belong sitting on  
the bench, I belong out there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 31-year-old Martinez, older brother of Boston ace Pedro  
Martinez, was 7-3 last year with Los Angeles before his season was 
cut short for rotator cuff surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Red Sox pitching coach Joe Kerrigan said Martinez will likely  
return the first or second week of July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
