<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Magellan Health Moving to Maryland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBIA, Md. (AP) -- Magellan Health Services, the nation's  
largest manager of health care plans, is moving its corporate 
headquarters from Atlanta to Maryland. 
</P>
<P>
	The move to Columbia, which is expected to be completed in the  
next few months, will bring about 600 jobs to Maryland over the 
next 2 1/2 years. 
</P>
<P>
	``With so many individuals already employed here in Maryland  
through our subsidiary, Magellan Behavioral Health, it is a natural 
fit to relocate our corporate headquarters here as well,'' Dr. 
Henry T. Harbin, president and chief executive, said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Magellan already has more than 900 employees in Maryland.  
</P>
<P>
	Harbin also said proximity to Washington and the center of the  
nation's health care policy-making was also a factor in the move. 
</P>
<P>
	Magellan was also lured by a $2.8 million grant from Maryland's  
Sunny Day Fund, which aims to stimulate economic growth. 
</P>
<P>
	Magellan Health Services Inc. is a $1.5 billion company with  
more than 11,000 employees nationwide. Its three main businesses 
are Magellan Specialty Health, which manages the care of 
individuals with chronic medical conditions; Magellan Behavioral 
Health, the nation's largest manager of mental health and substance 
abuse treatment programs; and MENTOR, which provides home and 
community-based services. 

</P>
</TEXT>
