<HEADLINE> Cincinnati Football Player Indicted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- University of Cincinnati football player  
DeMarco McCleskey was indicted on charges of raping a UC student in 
her dormitory room. 
</P>
<P>
	McCleskey, 18, was indicted Friday on two counts of rape and one  
count of aggravated burglary. If convicted, he could be sentenced 
to a maximum of 30 years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said a 19-year-old woman reported that McCleskey entered  
her dormitory room between 1:30 a.m. and 2:30 a.m. on May 9 and 
forced her to have sex. The woman said she knew McCleskey and had 
previously turned down his request for a date. 
</P>
<P>
	McCleskey, from Claremore, Okla., has denied the allegations and  
is out of jail on $10,000 bond. He has been suspended indefinitely 
from the team. 
</P>
<P>
	McCleskey was UC's top running back last season and was named to  
Conference USA's all-freshman team. He rushed for 861 yards and 11 
touchdowns on 162 carries and led the Cincinnati Bearcats in 
rushing and scoring last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
