<HEADLINE> Location of Kosovo Refugees in US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	With the arrival Friday of 483 Kosovo refugees at Fort Dix,  
N.J., 4,198 are now in the United States, 693 placed in homes in 16 
states, the State Department said. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. government has offered to take in up to 20,000 refugees  
from camps in Macedonia, where they fled after being forced from 
their homes in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo. Officials say 450 
more are to arrive in the next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Here is where the current Kosovo refugees are living:  
</P>
<P>
	At Fort Dix awaiting processing, 3,505.  
</P>
<P>
	Arizona, 11.  
</P>
<P>
	California, 65.  
</P>
<P>
	Connecticut, 11.  
</P>
<P>
	Florida, 50.  
</P>
<P>
	Idaho, 6.  
</P>
<P>
	Illinois, 20.  
</P>
<P>
	Kentucky, 14.  
</P>
<P>
	Michigan, 26  
</P>
<P>
	New Jersey, 81.  
</P>
<P>
	New York, 290.  
</P>
<P>
	North Carolina, 19.  
</P>
<P>
	Ohio, 5.  
</P>
<P>
	Texas, 57.  
</P>
<P>
	Virginia, 21.  
</P>
<P>
	Washington, 7.  
</P>
<P>
	Wisconsin, 10.  
</P>
