<HEADLINE> AP's Sullivan Gets Abidjan Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tim Sullivan, who has covered West Africa for  
The Associated Press for two years, has been named chief of bureau 
in Abidjan, Ivory Coast. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Thursday by AP President Louis D.  
Boccardi. 
</P>
<P>
	Sullivan, 33, joined the AP in New York in 1993. He worked on  
the International Desk before being assigned to Abidjan in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	A native of Concord, Mass., Sullivan is a graduate of Georgetown  
University. Before joining the AP, he worked as a teacher in South 
Africa and as a reporter for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram in Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	He succeeds Ian Stewart, who is recovering from wounds suffered  
in an attack in Sierra Leone that killed APTN Producer Myles 
Tierney in January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
