<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 8 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened narrowly higher. The  
Dow Jones industrial average is up eight points in today's early 
going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 5-3 lead 
over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up ten points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is up fractionally. 
</P>
<P>
	There is an absence of market-moving news today: no big economic  
reports, and no earth-shattering corporate combinations. 
</P>
<P>
	And analysts say because of that, the market will likely  
continue its recent drifting pattern. 
</P>
<P>
	This week has seen relatively low trading volume, small moves by  
the major market averages, and little in the way of market 
volatility. 
</P>
<P>
	The only difference today, perhaps, is that today is a  
double-witching expiration session, in which certain stock and 
index options expire. 
</P>
<P>
	That market phenomenon could boost trading levels somewhat.  
</P>
<P>
	Elsewhere, bond prices are higher. And overseas stock markets  
are mixed. 
</P>
