<P>
	Stocks End Mixed; Dow Down 37.46  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were mixed today as investors,  
worried about the effect rising interest rates might have on 
big-name stocks, moved money into small-cap issues. The Dow Jones 
industrial average closed down 37.46 at 10,829.28. Broader stock 
indicators were mixed. Most indexes were lower, but advancers 
outnumbered decliners on the New York Stock Exchange. Advancers and 
decliers were about even on the Nasdaq stock market. The Nasdaq 
composite fell 21.59 to 2,520.64. ``Some of the money coming out of 
the large-cap stocks is just looking for a new home,'' said Tony 
Cecin, director of institutional trading at Piper Jaffray in 
Minneapolis. Today was a ``double witching'' day, when stock and 
index options expire and traders adjust their portfolios. There was 
little news to affect the overall market. 

</P>
