announced today. Under the agreement, TransAlliance will make 
needed changes in its computer systems so that all its bank 
customers will be able to successfully complete their Year 2000 
testing by June 30 -- the deadline set for banks by the federal 
government. TransAlliance also agreed to have its own systems ready 
by that date. 

