chairman, today called ``ridiculous'' suggestions that AOL plotted 
with the government to say when the Justice Department first 
learned of his $10 billion purchase of Netscape. Case was 
interviewed today in preparation for the next phase of the trial of 
the government's antitrust suit against Microsoft Corp. Microsoft 
lawyers focused on AOL's purchase of Internet pioneer Netscape, 
which was publicly announced last November, after executives from 
both AOL and Netscape testified against Microsoft. 

</P>
