<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Roll Call on Gun Background Checks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The 50-50 roll call by which the Senate voted Thursday to  
require background checks for all firearms transactions at all gun 
shows and pawn shops. Vice President Al Gore broke the tie and the 
amendment was approved. 
</P>
<P>
	A ``yes'' vote was to impose the restrictions and a ``no'' was  
against the restrictions. 
</P>
<P>
	Voting ``yes'' were 44 Democrats and 6 Republicans.  
</P>
<P>
	Voting ``no'' were 1 Democrat and 49 Republicans.  

</P>
<P>
                             *Alabama    	
</P>
<P>
